headline: First Solar drops 13% on risk of Tesla’s solar push
summary: Investing.com -- Shares of First Solar are down more than 13% on Thursday on the prospect of Tesla building large-scale solar manufacturing capacity. Tesla’s push could weigh on long-term pricing expectations of First Solar. BMO Capital Markets downgraded the stock to Market Perform from Outperform cutting its price target on First Solar to $263 from $285.
